SIMPLE: sanguinary
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanguinary
<hw>San"gui*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sanguinarius</ets>, fr. <ets>sanguis</ets> blood: cf. F.
<ets>sanguinaire</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Attended with much
bloodshed; bloody; murderous; <as>as, a <ex>sanguinary</ex> war,
contest, or battle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We may not propagate religion by wars, or by <qex>sanguinary</qex>
persecutions to force consciences.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bloodthirsty; cruel; eager to shed blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Passion . . . makes us brutal and <qex>sanguinary</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Broome.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Bloody; murderous; bloodthirsty; cruel.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanguinary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sanguinary
<hw>San"gui*na*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>herba
sanguinaria</ets> an herb that stanches blood: cf. F.
<ets>sanguinaire</ets>. See <er>Sanguinary</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The yarrow.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The Sanguinaria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1275 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><ent>Sanguine</ent>⟦br⟧
